ete review.\n\n---\n\n# Code Review: `improve-context-management` Branch -- Strategy Layer\n\n## Scope\n\nBranch `improve-context-management` vs HEAD, filtered to:\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/` (all files)\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/` (committed.go, temporary.go)\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session/` (phase.go, state.go)\n\n42 files changed, ~1144 insertions, ~1127 deletions.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis change threads `context.Context` through approximately 80+ function signatures across the strategy, checkpoint, and session packages. It replaces ad-hoc `context.Background()` calls with properly propagated contexts, enabling cancellation, deadlines, and tracing throughout the call stack. The refactoring also renames `ctx StepContext` parameters to `step StepContext` where the name would shadow the new `context.Context` parameter.\n\n---\n\n## Critical (Must Fix)\n\n### C1. sync.Once captures first caller's context for git subprocess execution\n\n**`/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go:33-42`**\n\n`getStateStore(ctx)` passes the caller's `context.Context` into `sync.Once`. Inside the closure, `NewStateStore(ctx)` calls `getGitCommonDir(ctx)` which runs `exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"git\", \"rev-parse\", \"--git-common-dir\")`. If the first caller's context is already cancelled or is cancelled during the subprocess execution, the git command fails and the error is cached permanently by `sync.Once`. All subsequent callers will receive the cached error, even though they pass valid contexts.\n\n```go\n// manual_commit.go:33-42\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) getStateStore(ctx context.Context) (*session.StateStore, error) {\n    s.stateStoreOnce.Do(func() {\n        store, err := session.NewStateStore(ctx)  // ctx from first caller only\n        if err != nil {\n            s.stateStoreErr = fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create state store: %w\", err)\n            return\n        }\n  